=== KEY CONCEPTS ===
1. Liquidity is provided in specific price bands/ranges
2. Only positions with current price in their range earn fees
3. As price moves, different positions become active/inactive
4. Fees are distributed proportionally to active liquidity
5. Narrower ranges = higher capital efficiency but more rebalancing
